### Why Not the Alternatives

| Option | Why Rejected |
|---|---|
| **Azure AI Search (external)** | Requires separate Azure subscription, index provisioning, and data sync pipeline. Dataverse Search already uses Azure Cognitive Search internally ‚Äî duplicating the infrastructure is unnecessary cost and complexity for this scale. |
| **Azure Function** | Adds infrastructure, deployment pipeline, and maintenance overhead. Power Automate covers the orchestration need without custom code. Use only if Soundex expression functions are insufficient in PA. |
| **ForAll + client-side filter (current approach)** | Rejected by scale constraint. O(n) Dataverse calls with 100k+ records will time out and is architecturally unsafe. |
| **Power Fx only** | Impossible ‚Äî no fuzzy/phonetic primitives exist. |
| **FetchXML in Power Automate** | FetchXML supports `like`, `begins-with`, `ends-with` ‚Äî no fuzzy, no Soundex. Useful only for exact mode. |

